          MODULE=vim-repeat
         VERSION=1.2
          SOURCE=$MODULE-$VERSION.tar.gz
 SOURCE_URL_FULL=https://github.com/tpope/vim-repeat/archive/v$VERSION.tar.gz
      SOURCE_VFY=sha256:2bf7435dfdb7c6bfa87df228aaad4823698d9f00ca454f8f5d1903c63716f3ca
        WEB_SITE=https://github.com/tpope/vim-repeat/
         ENTERED=20200817
         UPDATED=20200817
           SHORT="Enable repeating supported plugin maps with ."

cat << EOF
If you've ever tried using the . command after a plugin map, you were likely
disappointed to discover it only repeated the last native command inside that
map, rather than the map as a whole. That disappointment ends today.
Repeat.vim remaps . in a way that plugins can tap into it.
EOF
